@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1 class="mb-4">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>
    The Most Common Bank of Australia (MCBA) is committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring
    that your personal and financial information is handled securely and responsibly. This Privacy Policy
    outlines how we collect, store, use, and protect your data when you use our Internet Banking services.
</p>

<h4 class="mt-4">1. Information We Collect</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Personal information such as your name, address, contact details, and Tax File Number (TFN).</li>
    <li>Account and transaction information including deposits, withdrawals, transfers, and BillPay activity.</li>
    <li>Login details such as your Login ID and securely hashed password.</li>
    <li>Technical data such as session identifiers and browser metadata to ensure secure access.</li>
</ul>

<h4 class="mt-4">2. How Your Information Is Used</h4>
<ul>
    <li>To verify your identity and manage your customer account.</li>
    <li>To process transactions, including deposits, withdrawals, transfers, and bill payments.</li>
    <li>To provide customer support and notify you about important account changes or updates.</li>
    <li>To maintain the security and integrity of our banking systems.</li>
</ul>

<h4 class="mt-4">3. Data Security</h4>
<p>
    All customer passwords are stored in a securely <strong>hashed and salted format</strong> using
    Microsoft’s PBKDF2 implementation via <code>SimpleHashing.Net</code>.
    Access to your data is restricted to authorised users, and all sensitive communication is encrypted.
</p>

<h4 class="mt-4">4. Data Sharing</h4>
<p>
    MCBA does not sell or rent customer information. Data may be shared only with trusted service providers
    or regulatory authorities when legally required to do so.
</p>

<h4 class="mt-4">5. Cookies and Session Management</h4>
<p>
    The website uses session cookies to manage secure login sessions. These cookies do not store personal
    data and expire automatically when you log out or close your browser.
</p>

<h4 class="mt-4">6. Your Rights</h4>
<p>
    You may access and update your personal information anytime through the <strong>My Profile</strong> section
    of your account. If you believe your data has been misused or is inaccurate, please contact MCBA support.
</p>

<h4 class="mt-4">7. Updates to This Policy</h4>
<p>
    This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically to reflect system improvements or changes in
    legal obligations. The latest version will always be available on this page.
</p>

